1
00:00:00,795 --> 00:00:02,338
Conan and Ran...

2
00:00:02,422 --> 00:00:05,341
were supposed to have a meal
with Ran's mother, the lawyer Kisaki.

3
00:00:05,633 --> 00:00:09,429
We were waiting at the apartment building
where Ms. Kisaki had a work appointment.

4
00:00:10,096 --> 00:00:13,308
And there, by chance,
we ran into Masumi Sera.

5
00:00:13,725 --> 00:00:17,937
At Sera's request, Ran ended up
helping her with an investigation.

6
00:00:19,897 --> 00:00:24,152
As part of it, we were searching
for one of the building's residents...

7
00:00:24,736 --> 00:00:27,447
Ah... Wak! Ms. Wakana!

8
00:00:29,240 --> 00:00:33,202
Stay with me!
Ms. Wakana! Ms. Wakana!

9
00:00:33,286 --> 00:00:35,788
Wa... ka...

10
00:00:40,168 --> 00:00:46,174
♪~

11
00:00:53,181 --> 00:00:56,392
Cutting through the dark shadows and gloom,
the light of deduction shines.

12
00:00:56,809 --> 00:01:00,813
Sera's deduction and one more mystery,
a clever trick you can't even watch unfold.

13
00:01:00,897 --> 00:01:02,398
Seeing through the one and only truth.

14
00:01:02,482 --> 00:01:04,108
Looks like a kid, mind of an adult.

15
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:07,111
His name is Detective Conan!

16
00:02:31,745 --> 00:02:37,751
~♪

17
00:02:39,353 --> 00:02:42,453
"The Restroom Where Ran Also Collapsed (Part 2)".

18
00:02:45,509 --> 00:02:47,553
A detective?

19
00:02:48,887 --> 00:02:51,014
Wh... what's going on here, Rumi?
- Kenya Settsu (22), University student

20
00:02:51,098 --> 00:02:53,434
There was a rumor that you were still seeing Wakana...
- Rumi Kitao (21), University student

21
00:02:53,517 --> 00:02:56,395
behind everyone's back,
so I...

22
00:02:56,478 --> 00:02:57,938
Rumi, you...

23
00:02:58,021 --> 00:02:59,648
I'm... I'm sorry.

24
00:03:00,482 --> 00:03:02,151
Anyway...

25
00:03:03,235 --> 00:03:04,445
Argh...

26
00:03:04,528 --> 00:03:08,866
The situation is, one of you... is the culprit. That's what I'm saying.
- Mitsuaki Kaga (22), University student

27
00:03:08,949 --> 00:03:10,409
Uh...

28
00:03:10,701 --> 00:03:12,578
That's true, certainly...

29
00:03:13,245 --> 00:03:15,664
but there's another possibility too.

30
00:03:16,457 --> 00:03:17,875
Hey, Ms. Rumi.

31
00:03:17,958 --> 00:03:19,543
Hm... huh?

32
00:03:19,626 --> 00:03:22,296
I found this photo in the living room...

33
00:03:23,172 --> 00:03:25,883
In the picture, all four of you
are wearing glasses,

34
00:03:25,966 --> 00:03:28,302
so why isn't anyone wearing them now?

35
00:03:28,594 --> 00:03:31,680
That's a photo from about two years ago.

36
00:03:31,764 --> 00:03:34,141
Everyone switched
to contacts since then.

37
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:36,101
Huh...

38
00:03:39,229 --> 00:03:41,857
What? The murder weapon was found?

39
00:03:41,940 --> 00:03:44,526
Yes. There was a golf club
in the living room...

40
00:03:44,610 --> 00:03:47,946
and it tested positive for blood.

41
00:03:48,030 --> 00:03:51,033
Also, from the kitchen sink drain...

42
00:03:51,116 --> 00:03:53,869
a small bottle of chloroform
and a syringe.

43
00:03:53,952 --> 00:03:56,371
And from the bathroom drain...

44
00:03:56,455 --> 00:03:58,874
a liquid that looked like red paint.

45
00:03:58,957 --> 00:04:02,795
Ah... red paint?
Why would that be there?

46
00:04:02,878 --> 00:04:05,964
Hmm... And the shower being
left running in the tub...

47
00:04:06,048 --> 00:04:07,841
is strange too.

48
00:04:07,925 --> 00:04:11,845
If you wanted to fudge the time of death
without lowering the rectal temperature...

49
00:04:11,929 --> 00:04:14,014
you'd normally run it over the body.

50
00:04:14,890 --> 00:04:18,852
Just what the hell
is going on with this case?

51
00:04:19,394 --> 00:04:21,021
Hey, Ran.

52
00:04:21,104 --> 00:04:24,483
The one who used the spare key
to open the door to this room...

53
00:04:24,566 --> 00:04:25,734
was Ms. Rumi, right?

54
00:04:25,818 --> 00:04:27,402
Uh... yeah.

55
00:04:27,486 --> 00:04:30,030
Did she fumble with it at all?

56
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:32,407
No, it was pretty normal.

57
00:04:32,491 --> 00:04:35,202
She seemed used to coming in.

58
00:04:35,285 --> 00:04:39,873
But you know, when you take the key
out of your pocket like this...

59
00:04:39,957 --> 00:04:41,291
Ah!

60
00:04:42,417 --> 00:04:44,211
Ahh!
Hm?

61
00:04:44,545 --> 00:04:47,589
Sorry! Could you grab it?

62
00:04:47,673 --> 00:04:48,799
...Geez.

63
00:04:48,882 --> 00:04:50,717
What a handful.

64
00:04:50,801 --> 00:04:52,803
Ah... sorry.

65
00:04:53,053 --> 00:04:55,222
Thanks for picking it up.

66
00:04:55,764 --> 00:04:56,765
Here you go.

67
00:04:56,849 --> 00:04:58,600
Don't go dropping it again.

68
00:04:58,892 --> 00:04:59,893
Hm...

69
00:05:00,477 --> 00:05:04,606
I knew it... So that's how it is.

70
00:05:05,566 --> 00:05:09,403
If I figured it out,
then she probably did too...

71
00:05:09,486 --> 00:05:11,613
Huh? A phone call?

72
00:05:12,781 --> 00:05:13,991
With who?

73
00:05:15,117 --> 00:05:19,037
Hey, is my deduction wrong?

74
00:05:22,416 --> 00:05:23,959
In any case...

75
00:05:24,042 --> 00:05:28,463
the only ones who could have bludgeoned
the owner of this place, Wakana Hashitani,

76
00:05:28,839 --> 00:05:31,592
to death in the bathroom...
are the man who dated the victim

77
00:05:31,675 --> 00:05:35,637
until six months ago and still had
a spare key, Mr. Settsu, and...

78
00:05:36,179 --> 00:05:40,183
the man who was drinking here with
the victim until five this morning,

79
00:05:40,267 --> 00:05:43,520
who may have taken the key,
Mr. Kaga.

80
00:05:43,604 --> 00:05:45,272
Just you two.

81
00:05:45,856 --> 00:05:47,107
You were both supposed to meet...

82
00:05:47,190 --> 00:05:50,402
the victim in the building lobby
at noon...

83
00:05:50,485 --> 00:05:53,655
to have lunch together,
apparently...

84
00:05:53,989 --> 00:05:58,327
Mr. Settsu got up to use the restroom
30 minutes before the meeting time,

85
00:05:58,410 --> 00:06:01,788
and Mr. Kaga showed up
in the lobby in the early afternoon,

86
00:06:01,872 --> 00:06:04,166
but his movements before that
are unknown.

87
00:06:04,666 --> 00:06:06,251
Now, spit it out.

88
00:06:06,335 --> 00:06:09,171
One of you two did it, didn't you?

89
00:06:09,254 --> 00:06:11,214
W... wait a second.

90
00:06:11,298 --> 00:06:14,843
Wakana was found collapsed
in a bathroom...

91
00:06:14,927 --> 00:06:16,219
full of chloroform, right?

92
00:06:16,303 --> 00:06:17,763
If we were the culprits,

93
00:06:17,846 --> 00:06:21,600
why would we leave the bathroom
in a state like that?

94
00:06:21,683 --> 00:06:22,809
Hmph.
Ah...

95
00:06:23,101 --> 00:06:27,648
To knock out Ms. Rumi, who'd come
to fetch the victim later,

96
00:06:27,731 --> 00:06:31,276
and delay the discovery
of the body, right?

97
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:35,822
The more it's delayed, the wider
the estimated time of death becomes.

98
00:06:36,198 --> 00:06:39,326
And this Rumi here claims she was...

99
00:06:39,409 --> 00:06:43,288
with some so-called detective
right up until she went to fetch Wakana,

100
00:06:43,497 --> 00:06:45,332
but who knows if that's even true.

101
00:06:45,624 --> 00:06:47,167
Ke... Kenya.

102
00:06:47,709 --> 00:06:51,129
If it's Rumi, who used to share
this room with Wakana,

103
00:06:51,213 --> 00:06:53,882
she might still have a key,

104
00:06:53,966 --> 00:06:57,844
and she could be in cahoots with that
detective, getting their stories straight.

105
00:06:58,053 --> 00:07:00,639
It's all way too convenient.

106
00:07:00,722 --> 00:07:03,934
Suddenly butting in, claiming Rumi
has an alibi because they were...

107
00:07:04,017 --> 00:07:06,561
together the whole time...
What a load of nonsense.

108
00:07:06,645 --> 00:07:10,774
No. I never said Ms. Rumi had an alibi.

109
00:07:10,857 --> 00:07:12,859
Huh?
Huh?

110
00:07:13,527 --> 00:07:16,947
If Ran, who went with her
to fetch Ms. Wakana,

111
00:07:17,030 --> 00:07:19,533
was the one who found
Ms. Wakana's body,

112
00:07:19,616 --> 00:07:23,078
then I'm simply saying the culprit
is one of you two men.

113
00:07:23,412 --> 00:07:27,374
But if that body
wasn't Ms. Wakana's...

114
00:07:27,791 --> 00:07:29,126
then that's another story.

115
00:07:29,209 --> 00:07:30,669
Huh?
Ah...

116
00:07:30,752 --> 00:07:32,295
Wh... what did you say?

117
00:07:32,629 --> 00:07:36,675
But I really did see
Ms. Wakana's body...

118
00:07:36,758 --> 00:07:39,553
You just think you did,
don't you?

119
00:07:39,636 --> 00:07:42,723
You'd never met Ms. Wakana
before, right?

120
00:07:42,806 --> 00:07:44,182
That's true, but...

121
00:07:44,474 --> 00:07:47,102
And the body was face-down...

122
00:07:47,185 --> 00:07:50,939
with a face mask on,
a towel wrapped around the head,

123
00:07:51,023 --> 00:07:54,443
and on top of that, the bathroom was
hazy with steam from the shower, right?

124
00:07:55,110 --> 00:07:58,030
Even if someone else
was impersonating her,

125
00:07:58,697 --> 00:08:00,532
I don't think you'd have noticed.

126
00:08:01,241 --> 00:08:04,077
Right? You think so too,
don't you, Conan?

127
00:08:04,161 --> 00:08:05,412
Huh... yeah.

128
00:08:06,079 --> 00:08:08,206
Could this girl possibly...

129
00:08:08,457 --> 00:08:10,667
Impersonating her, you say...

130
00:08:10,751 --> 00:08:13,587
Who exactly are you saying
was pretending to be Wakana?

131
00:08:14,087 --> 00:08:16,673
She was collapsed
in nothing but a bath towel, right?

132
00:08:16,757 --> 00:08:21,053
Ah, yes. I'm sure it was a woman,
there's no doubt about that.

133
00:08:21,136 --> 00:08:23,555
In that case, the only one
who could have done it...

134
00:08:23,638 --> 00:08:26,099
is the one who came to fetch
Ms. Wakana with Ran...

135
00:08:27,851 --> 00:08:29,770
There's no one but Ms. Rumi.

136
00:08:30,562 --> 00:08:31,980
Huh?!

137
00:08:32,064 --> 00:08:33,982
Huh?
Ah...

138
00:08:34,524 --> 00:08:37,903
In other words, when Ms. Rumi
came here with Ran,

139
00:08:37,986 --> 00:08:40,405
she pretended she was
heading to the living room,

140
00:08:40,739 --> 00:08:45,077
and sent Ran toward the bedroom
on the opposite side,

141
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:46,995
having her search for Ms. Wakana.

142
00:08:48,371 --> 00:08:51,416
Then, watching for her chance,
she slipped into the bathroom,

143
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:55,170
stripped down to a single bath towel,
put a mask on her face,

144
00:08:58,340 --> 00:09:00,801
wrapped a towel around her head...

145
00:09:01,676 --> 00:09:04,513
and dripped red paint near her head...

146
00:09:04,971 --> 00:09:07,474
to make herself look dead.

147
00:09:09,142 --> 00:09:12,979
Then, timing it for when Ran
would come to search the bathroom,

148
00:09:13,647 --> 00:09:17,275
she sprayed out the chloroform
she'd loaded into the syringe,

149
00:09:17,901 --> 00:09:19,528
letting it vaporize...

150
00:09:21,363 --> 00:09:24,950
Are you okay...? Ah, Ms. Wakana.

151
00:09:26,910 --> 00:09:29,454
And when Ran entered the bathroom...

152
00:09:31,456 --> 00:09:33,208
she knocked her out.

153
00:09:34,668 --> 00:09:39,089
Of course, she held her breath
the entire time.

154
00:09:39,172 --> 00:09:42,342
Hold on. Where was the victim
during all this...?

155
00:09:42,634 --> 00:09:44,803
Sleeping in the living room,
wouldn't you say?

156
00:09:44,886 --> 00:09:48,640
You know, Ms. Wakana
got drunk before too...

157
00:09:48,723 --> 00:09:50,058
and fell asleep on the balcony...

158
00:09:50,142 --> 00:09:52,853
off the living room,
remember her saying that?

159
00:09:53,228 --> 00:09:57,274
If Ms. Rumi knew that Ms. Wakana
and Mr. Kaga had been drinking here...

160
00:09:57,357 --> 00:09:59,401
until this morning...

161
00:10:04,072 --> 00:10:08,410
then she could have called once
she figured Mr. Kaga had left,

162
00:10:08,827 --> 00:10:13,206
lured her out to the balcony
to sober up,

163
00:10:13,623 --> 00:10:17,335
and gotten her to fall asleep
right there.

164
00:10:18,003 --> 00:10:19,004
That's right.

165
00:10:19,337 --> 00:10:23,425
After Ran was knocked out,
Ms. Rumi left the bathroom...

166
00:10:23,717 --> 00:10:26,595
aired out the chloroform for a while,

167
00:10:26,678 --> 00:10:29,264
washed away the red paint,

168
00:10:29,931 --> 00:10:34,436
got dressed again, woke Ms. Wakana
who was sleeping in the living room,

169
00:10:34,936 --> 00:10:39,691
and told her "some girl I don't know
has collapsed," sending her to the bathroom.

170
00:10:41,067 --> 00:10:43,570
Then, as Ms. Wakana
stood there startled...

171
00:10:44,070 --> 00:10:48,450
by Ran lying collapsed, she bludgeoned her
from behind with the golf club...

172
00:10:49,159 --> 00:10:51,328
stripped her down to a bath towel,

173
00:10:51,411 --> 00:10:54,956
put a mask on her face,
wrapped a towel around her head,

174
00:10:55,415 --> 00:10:59,002
and once again filled the bathroom
with chloroform...

175
00:10:59,794 --> 00:11:02,589
This time, she really breathed it in
and passed out,

176
00:11:02,923 --> 00:11:06,176
waiting for them
to come rushing in.

177
00:11:06,968 --> 00:11:10,263
After all, who would think
that the person who went...

178
00:11:10,347 --> 00:11:11,723
to fetch the victim...

179
00:11:11,806 --> 00:11:14,559
had played dead
in such a short time?

180
00:11:14,643 --> 00:11:17,771
N... no, I didn't do anything like that...

181
00:11:17,854 --> 00:11:20,649
A... and the reason I went
to the living room...

182
00:11:20,732 --> 00:11:22,776
was because Kenya called me...

183
00:11:22,984 --> 00:11:25,153
But even without the call,

184
00:11:25,237 --> 00:11:28,865
you were planning to look for
Mr. Settsu's lost item there, weren't you?

185
00:11:28,949 --> 00:11:30,450
Uh... yeah.

186
00:11:30,533 --> 00:11:34,329
Even without the spare key
you got from Mr. Settsu,

187
00:11:34,412 --> 00:11:37,082
you were planning to use the key
from when you shared the room...

188
00:11:37,165 --> 00:11:39,584
with Ms. Wakana, saying something
like "I'd been meaning to...

189
00:11:39,668 --> 00:11:41,670
return it today," weren't you?

190
00:11:42,045 --> 00:11:45,257
And if you hired me
as a detective...

191
00:11:45,340 --> 00:11:49,177
to have someone witness you
playing dead in the first place,

192
00:11:49,261 --> 00:11:50,971
then it all adds up.

193
00:11:51,346 --> 00:11:53,098
Though this time, you ended up
making Ran fill the role.

194
00:11:53,098 --> 00:11:55,976
Though this time, you ended up
making Ran fill the role.
(phone ringing)

195
00:11:57,018 --> 00:12:00,855
The little sister who was actually
supposed to come to the dinner today...

196
00:12:00,939 --> 00:12:02,857
could have played the part too,

197
00:12:02,941 --> 00:12:06,861
but with your sister, there'd be
too much risk of being found out,

198
00:12:06,945 --> 00:12:09,823
so you decided to have
a stranger do it instead, I'd say.

199
00:12:09,906 --> 00:12:12,033
N... no, I didn't...

200
00:12:12,117 --> 00:12:13,743
Inspector.
Ah.

201
00:12:14,327 --> 00:12:16,621
There were fingerprints
on the chloroform bottle.

202
00:12:16,705 --> 00:12:18,373
Huh?
Hey.

203
00:12:18,456 --> 00:12:22,002
Don't tell me they're
Rumi Kitao's fingerprints?

204
00:12:22,085 --> 00:12:24,004
Y... yes.
Huh?

205
00:12:24,504 --> 00:12:27,966
A splendid deduction.
Not bad, kid.

206
00:12:28,049 --> 00:12:29,634
Ah... yeah.

207
00:12:29,968 --> 00:12:31,136
That deduction...

208
00:12:33,221 --> 00:12:35,557
Doesn't it sit a little uneasy with you?

209
00:12:44,873 --> 00:12:45,916
Huh?

210
00:12:46,374 --> 00:12:48,126
S... sit uneasy?

211
00:12:48,210 --> 00:12:50,045
Wh... what are you talking about?

212
00:12:50,128 --> 00:12:52,088
Ah, no, it's not me...

213
00:12:52,422 --> 00:12:55,467
Shinichi heard about the case
from Conan,

214
00:12:55,550 --> 00:12:57,385
and he told me to say that
over the phone...

215
00:12:57,469 --> 00:12:59,888
Ah, I'll put it on speaker now.

216
00:13:00,138 --> 00:13:01,890
Shinichi Kudo...

217
00:13:02,224 --> 00:13:05,143
I don't know who the hell you are,
but outsiders should stay out of...

218
00:13:05,227 --> 00:13:07,270
There are three things
that don't sit right.

219
00:13:07,354 --> 00:13:09,397
Hmph...
Hm...

220
00:13:09,898 --> 00:13:11,566
You said she led the victim...

221
00:13:11,650 --> 00:13:15,237
to sleep in the living room
as had happened before,

222
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:19,074
but that was just something
that happened once in the past.

223
00:13:19,574 --> 00:13:22,577
You can lure someone to the living room
over the phone,

224
00:13:22,661 --> 00:13:25,413
but I doubt you could conveniently
get them to fall asleep.

225
00:13:26,164 --> 00:13:28,917
And even if she did happen
to fall asleep,

226
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,669
whether she'd stay asleep...

227
00:13:30,752 --> 00:13:33,713
until Rumi came to fetch her
is also doubtful.

228
00:13:34,005 --> 00:13:37,092
The doorbell at the entrance
could have woken her up.

229
00:13:37,175 --> 00:13:40,303
Then what if Ms. Rumi
came here well before...

230
00:13:40,387 --> 00:13:42,013
I arrived with her,

231
00:13:42,097 --> 00:13:45,433
and had already put Ms. Wakana
to sleep with chloroform?

232
00:13:45,517 --> 00:13:48,311
That way, a doorbell wouldn't
wake her, right?

233
00:13:48,395 --> 00:13:50,397
That's the second problem.

234
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:51,648
Huh?

235
00:13:51,731 --> 00:13:53,817
If that were the case,

236
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:56,027
why would Ms. Rumi
lock the front door...

237
00:13:56,111 --> 00:13:58,071
at all?
Ah.

238
00:13:58,446 --> 00:13:59,948
If Mr. Settsu...

239
00:14:00,031 --> 00:14:03,034
hadn't happened
to hand over the spare key,

240
00:14:03,118 --> 00:14:06,663
she'd have been forced to use
the key she'd failed to return to Ms. Wakana,

241
00:14:06,746 --> 00:14:10,583
and as the one holding it,
she'd be the first to be suspected, right?

242
00:14:10,834 --> 00:14:14,504
And if she'd put Ms. Wakana
to sleep beforehand,

243
00:14:14,587 --> 00:14:15,839
it would be safer...

244
00:14:15,922 --> 00:14:19,467
to have the sleeping Ms. Wakana herself
play the role of the body.

245
00:14:19,843 --> 00:14:22,512
There's no need for her to go
to the trouble of holding her breath...

246
00:14:22,595 --> 00:14:24,848
and playing the corpse herself.

247
00:14:24,931 --> 00:14:26,850
Hmm...
Ah...

248
00:14:27,517 --> 00:14:29,394
And the third...

249
00:14:29,477 --> 00:14:32,689
is that the body was lying face-down
in nothing but a bath towel.

250
00:14:33,898 --> 00:14:38,236
No one can fully picture
what they look like from behind.

251
00:14:39,154 --> 00:14:43,450
There could easily be a mole or birthmark
even you don't know about.

252
00:14:43,950 --> 00:14:48,079
If Ran saw it and realized it didn't match
the real person, it'd be over.

253
00:14:48,163 --> 00:14:52,542
For impersonating someone, it's the worst
possible outfit and the worst possible pose.

254
00:14:52,625 --> 00:14:56,338
B... but the body
had a mask on...

255
00:14:56,421 --> 00:14:59,132
and the culprit made it hard to see
with the steam.

256
00:14:59,215 --> 00:15:00,467
No matter how you look at it...

257
00:15:00,550 --> 00:15:02,135
That's exactly it.
Ah.

258
00:15:02,427 --> 00:15:06,681
If the body's face is hidden
and the view is obscured,

259
00:15:06,765 --> 00:15:09,934
people will suspect
it might have been someone else.

260
00:15:10,268 --> 00:15:13,146
That was precisely
the culprit's aim.

261
00:15:14,064 --> 00:15:17,359
Leaving the body in nothing but a bath towel
and lying it face-down...

262
00:15:17,692 --> 00:15:21,154
was to make the discoverer think
the body's face was being hidden,

263
00:15:21,237 --> 00:15:25,158
while also making it instantly clear
that the body was a woman.

264
00:15:25,742 --> 00:15:26,785
That way,

265
00:15:26,868 --> 00:15:29,621
whoever was impersonating
the body would have to be a woman,

266
00:15:29,704 --> 00:15:31,581
removing himself as a suspect,

267
00:15:31,664 --> 00:15:34,542
and pinning the crime on Ms. Rumi.

268
00:15:35,251 --> 00:15:38,880
Isn't that right?
Thirty minutes before the meeting time,

269
00:15:38,963 --> 00:15:41,883
you pretended to go to the restroom
and came up here,

270
00:15:41,966 --> 00:15:45,720
bludgeoned Ms. Wakana to death
and staged it with that trick...

271
00:15:46,054 --> 00:15:47,680
her ex-boyfriend...

272
00:15:47,764 --> 00:15:49,599
Ah.
Huh?

273
00:15:49,682 --> 00:15:51,393
Kenya Settsu.

274
00:15:51,684 --> 00:15:52,936
Huh?
Ah...

275
00:15:53,770 --> 00:15:56,189
Wh... what?
That's right.

276
00:15:56,731 --> 00:15:58,733
When you came here,

277
00:15:59,567 --> 00:16:03,238
you caught Ms. Wakana off guard, made her
breathe the chloroform, and put her to sleep...

278
00:16:03,905 --> 00:16:05,949
You carried Ms. Wakana
to the bathroom,

279
00:16:06,032 --> 00:16:08,743
stripped her down
to a single bath towel,

280
00:16:09,160 --> 00:16:12,914
put a mask on her face,
wrapped a towel around her head,

281
00:16:12,997 --> 00:16:15,291
and then bludgeoned her
with the golf club.

282
00:16:16,668 --> 00:16:19,963
After that, you just had to pour
the red paint down the bathroom drain,

283
00:16:20,547 --> 00:16:23,466
and fill the room with chloroform.

284
00:16:24,342 --> 00:16:26,928
You called Ms. Rumi,
who went to fetch her,

285
00:16:27,345 --> 00:16:28,763
sent her to the living room,

286
00:16:29,514 --> 00:16:32,642
and created a window of time as if
she'd been impersonating the body...

287
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:37,272
Then, after the crime, if Ms. Rumi's
fingerprints turned up...

288
00:16:37,355 --> 00:16:39,774
on the chloroform bottle
you'd hidden away,

289
00:16:40,608 --> 00:16:43,820
the police would fall
for the fake. That's the plan.

290
00:16:44,446 --> 00:16:47,323
By the way, the bottle
with her fingerprints on it...

291
00:16:47,866 --> 00:16:51,119
was probably something you got
Ms. Rumi to handle beforehand.

292
00:16:51,202 --> 00:16:55,206
If the two of you were dating,
just leaving it on the spice rack...

293
00:16:55,290 --> 00:16:57,792
would make it easy
to get her to touch it.

294
00:16:59,586 --> 00:17:02,672
H... hey, I don't know
who you are,

295
00:17:02,755 --> 00:17:05,175
but that trick could've been
pulled off by Kaga too...

296
00:17:05,258 --> 00:17:07,385
That's why I had Conan test it.

297
00:17:07,469 --> 00:17:08,470
Hm?

298
00:17:08,553 --> 00:17:10,138
T... test it?

299
00:17:11,014 --> 00:17:14,684
Remember when I had you guys
pick up that loose change?

300
00:17:14,767 --> 00:17:19,439
At that moment, I held out my palm
and gestured for you to hand it over, right?

301
00:17:19,856 --> 00:17:23,026
Mr. Kaga placed it
right in my palm,

302
00:17:23,109 --> 00:17:26,404
but Mr. Settsu put the change
in his own palm...

303
00:17:26,488 --> 00:17:29,407
and held it out for me to take, right?

304
00:17:29,491 --> 00:17:31,284
That's how I knew.

305
00:17:31,367 --> 00:17:33,912
Mr. Settsu couldn't judge
the distance,

306
00:17:33,995 --> 00:17:37,457
so he couldn't place the change
in my palm,

307
00:17:37,957 --> 00:17:41,002
and even though I was
holding my palm out,

308
00:17:41,085 --> 00:17:44,672
he set things up so I'd be the one
to grab the change.

309
00:17:45,381 --> 00:17:49,344
Well, Mr. Settsu also failed to hand
the spare key to Ms. Rumi...

310
00:17:49,427 --> 00:17:52,055
for the same reason,

311
00:17:52,138 --> 00:17:54,557
so it's no wonder
he did it that way.

312
00:17:54,641 --> 00:17:56,684
Wh... what on earth
are you talking about...

313
00:17:57,185 --> 00:17:58,853
Contacts.

314
00:17:58,937 --> 00:18:02,815
The contact lens in one of
Mr. Settsu's eyes has fallen out.

315
00:18:03,858 --> 00:18:05,235
It probably came out...

316
00:18:05,318 --> 00:18:09,322
when Ms. Wakana resisted as he tried
to make her breathe the chloroform.

317
00:18:09,405 --> 00:18:14,035
He frantically searched the floor
where it fell, but couldn't find it.

318
00:18:14,327 --> 00:18:16,246
Because...

319
00:18:16,329 --> 00:18:19,832
Ms. Wakana, who'd collapsed on the floor
after being made to breathe the drug,

320
00:18:19,916 --> 00:18:22,919
picked it up and hid it
as her consciousness faded.

321
00:18:23,211 --> 00:18:25,380
Hid it? Where?

322
00:18:25,463 --> 00:18:28,132
The victim was stripped naked
afterward, you know.

323
00:18:28,216 --> 00:18:32,762
You said it yourself, didn't you, Inspector?
That the body was strange.

324
00:18:33,263 --> 00:18:36,266
Ah! I see... a wink.

325
00:18:36,349 --> 00:18:39,561
The victim hid it
inside her own eye.

326
00:18:40,228 --> 00:18:42,605
Check the body immediately.
Yes, sir.

327
00:18:43,982 --> 00:18:46,776
Even if a contact lens turned up
in the room later,

328
00:18:47,360 --> 00:18:51,114
you were planning to play dumb,
claiming you dropped it back when...

329
00:18:51,197 --> 00:18:53,950
you were dating and never found it,
weren't you?

330
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:56,828
But with it inside her eye,

331
00:18:56,911 --> 00:19:01,082
and not in yours,
it's undeniable evidence.

332
00:19:01,666 --> 00:19:05,336
And being a contact lens,
your fingerprints are probably on it too.

333
00:19:05,420 --> 00:19:07,714
Hey, you've got to be kidding, Settsu.

334
00:19:08,047 --> 00:19:10,508
Why would you even kill Wakana...

335
00:19:10,592 --> 00:19:13,261
Weren't you two broken up?

336
00:19:13,344 --> 00:19:16,973
Yeah. So I could date
the chairman's daughter.

337
00:19:17,056 --> 00:19:20,184
Th... the chairman's daughter?
That first-year?

338
00:19:20,268 --> 00:19:23,896
Can you blame me? Wakana's parent
is just a managing director.

339
00:19:23,980 --> 00:19:27,900
She's the daughter of the chairman
of that company's affiliate group.

340
00:19:27,984 --> 00:19:31,738
If I could marry into that,
talk about marrying up.

341
00:19:31,821 --> 00:19:35,658
I'd already gotten a job offer there too,
so my career was set.

342
00:19:37,201 --> 00:19:41,414
But if you'd already broken up,
you didn't need to kill her, did you?

343
00:19:41,497 --> 00:19:44,167
Wakana was blackmailing me.
Huh?

344
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:46,002
If I made the other girl mine,

345
00:19:46,085 --> 00:19:49,505
she'd expose all my past misdeeds
to her.

346
00:19:49,589 --> 00:19:54,052
Before I dated Wakana, I'd made
quite a few women cry.

347
00:19:54,135 --> 00:19:56,012
Then what was I?

348
00:19:56,095 --> 00:19:58,348
Why did you even date me?

349
00:19:58,431 --> 00:20:02,518
Hmph. If a girl got killed
right after we broke up,

350
00:20:02,602 --> 00:20:04,479
I'd be the one under suspicion,
wouldn't I?

351
00:20:06,064 --> 00:20:07,440
By dating you...

352
00:20:07,523 --> 00:20:10,401
and spreading a rumor that I still
hadn't cut things off with Wakana,

353
00:20:10,777 --> 00:20:14,155
I'd have a motive for you to kill her
out of jealousy.

354
00:20:14,238 --> 00:20:17,617
Well, you got to date me, the great me,
for a whole six months.

355
00:20:17,867 --> 00:20:20,787
Make it a fond memo... ngh!

356
00:20:23,623 --> 00:20:25,458
Oh.
Ah.

357
00:20:27,794 --> 00:20:31,923
Ah, my bad.
When I hear such trash talk...

358
00:20:32,006 --> 00:20:35,635
my head starts to itch,
and my elbow just slipped.

359
00:20:36,010 --> 00:20:37,762
If you keep up this trash talk...

360
00:20:37,845 --> 00:20:39,347
my...
Eek!

361
00:20:39,430 --> 00:20:43,685
this time my backside might start itching,
and my knee just might slip out too.

362
00:20:43,768 --> 00:20:45,687
Would that be all right with you?

363
00:20:45,937 --> 00:20:47,146
No, sir...

364
00:20:47,730 --> 00:20:50,191
(Rumi sobbing)

365
00:20:54,362 --> 00:20:56,072
But I'm impressed.

366
00:20:56,155 --> 00:20:58,741
Seeing through that fake,
that's something.

367
00:20:58,825 --> 00:21:01,744
It wasn't me, it was Shinichi.

368
00:21:02,120 --> 00:21:06,624
Ah, no way. Shinichi's call
got cut off at some point.

369
00:21:06,708 --> 00:21:09,502
Ah, n... now that you mention it,
Shinichi said something.

370
00:21:09,877 --> 00:21:12,547
Mascara had run
from the corner of Ms. Wakana's eye,

371
00:21:12,630 --> 00:21:14,549
and that's how he noticed the fake.

372
00:21:14,632 --> 00:21:17,719
If you're going to put a mask on,
you have to remove the makeup,

373
00:21:17,802 --> 00:21:21,472
so the culprit realized that
and wiped off the lipstick,

374
00:21:21,556 --> 00:21:25,601
but if the culprit had been a woman,
there's no way she'd overlook the mascara.

375
00:21:26,060 --> 00:21:28,020
I'm sure since Sera...

376
00:21:28,104 --> 00:21:32,400
has never worn mascara herself,
she couldn't have noticed.

377
00:21:32,483 --> 00:21:33,901
I see.

378
00:21:38,197 --> 00:21:39,907
Shinichi's...

379
00:21:39,991 --> 00:21:42,577
never worn mascara either, though.

380
00:21:44,787 --> 00:21:50,793
♪~

381
00:22:59,111 --> 00:23:04,367
~♪

382
00:23:04,450 --> 00:23:08,329
What? You got caught up
in a murder case?

383
00:23:08,621 --> 00:23:11,541
Why didn't you tell me, your mother?

384
00:23:11,624 --> 00:23:14,210
Well, the detective Sera was there too,

385
00:23:14,794 --> 00:23:17,630
and in the end,
Kudo solved it for us.

386
00:23:17,713 --> 00:23:20,508
Ah...
Well then, I'll be going.

387
00:23:21,342 --> 00:23:22,718
Oh, that girl...

388
00:23:22,802 --> 00:23:25,263
Huh? Do you know Sera?

389
00:23:25,680 --> 00:23:30,434
Yes. Actually, I came down
to this lobby before noon...

390
00:23:30,518 --> 00:23:34,689
to tell you two that the meeting
was running long.

391
00:23:34,772 --> 00:23:37,400
But you two hadn't arrived yet,

392
00:23:37,483 --> 00:23:39,402
and that girl was on the phone...

393
00:23:39,485 --> 00:23:42,113
Huh? On the phone? With who?

394
00:23:42,196 --> 00:23:46,158
Who knows. She was adding "-nii"
after a name when she talked,

395
00:23:46,742 --> 00:23:48,744
so maybe it was her older brother?

396
00:23:51,789 --> 00:23:54,458
(whistle and crowd cheering)

397
00:23:55,626 --> 00:23:56,752
Whoa!
Wow...

398
00:23:57,169 --> 00:23:59,338
Watching a soccer game today...

399
00:23:59,422 --> 00:24:00,756
with your girlfriend?

400
00:24:01,090 --> 00:24:02,758
And then, player Sanada...

401
00:24:03,551 --> 00:24:08,097
aiming for the same upper-left corner
of the goal, fires a hard straight ball.

402
00:24:08,598 --> 00:24:10,057
Ahh~
Sanada!

403
00:24:10,141 --> 00:24:11,267
Don't mind, don't mind!

404
00:24:12,852 --> 00:24:14,020
That old guy...

405
00:24:14,103 --> 00:24:15,688
sure is suspicious.

406
00:24:15,937 --> 00:24:17,637
Next Conan,

407
00:24:17,637 --> 00:24:21,637
"Promise with the J-Leaguer".

408
00:24:37,037 --> 00:24:39,237
Next Conan's Hint:

409
00:24:39,237 --> 00:24:41,737
"Sanada Takahiro".

410
00:24:41,737 --> 00:24:43,537
Kudo, the genius of make-up.

411
00:24:43,537 --> 00:24:44,937
It's deduction based knowledge.
412
00:24:44,937 --> 00:24:46,537
Somehow I feel more upset.
